# 📌 Project Issues & Improvements

This repository is focused on demonstrating Java Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) concepts using compiled `.class` files.  
The following issues and improvements have been identified for future development.

---

# 🐞 Current Issues

## 1️⃣ Missing Source Code Files

### Problem
The repository currently contains only compiled `.class` files and does not include original `.java` source files.

### Impact
- Harder for beginners to understand the implementation
- Difficult to modify or debug the code
- Reduces readability and learning value

### Proposed Solution
Add all corresponding `.java` source files with proper folder structure.

---

## 2️⃣ Lack of Code Documentation

### Problem
Most classes and methods do not contain comments or explanations.

### Impact
- New contributors may struggle to understand the logic
- Learning experience becomes less effective

### Proposed Solution
Add:
- Inline comments
- Method descriptions
- Concept explanations

---

## 3️⃣ No Organized Package Structure

### Problem
All class files are placed together without proper package organization.

### Impact
- Difficult to maintain large projects
- Poor scalability

### Proposed Solution
Organize files into packages such as:

```bash
encapsulation/
inheritance/
polymorphism/
abstraction/
```

---

## 4️⃣ Limited Real-World Examples

### Problem
The project mainly demonstrates basic OOP concepts without practical applications.

### Impact
- Concepts may feel theoretical
- Limited industry-level exposure

### Proposed Solution
Add mini projects like:
- Student Management System
- Banking System
- Library Management System

---

## 5️⃣ No Build Tool Integration

### Problem
The project does not use build tools like Maven or Gradle.

### Impact
- Dependency management becomes difficult
- Less aligned with modern Java development practices

### Proposed Solution
Integrate:
- Maven
OR
- Gradle

---

## 6️⃣ No Unit Testing

### Problem
There are no automated tests available.

### Impact
- Harder to verify correctness
- Bugs may go unnoticed

### Proposed Solution
Add:
- JUnit test cases
- Automated testing workflows

---

